  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0da7\u0dca \u0da7\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dca \u0d91\u0d9a\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dcf\u0da9\u0db8\u0dca \u0d89\u0d9c\u0dd9\u0db1 \u0db1\u0ddc\u0d9c\u0dad\u0ddc\u0dad\u0dca \u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0db1\u0dba \u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0da7\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "If you do not learn the lessons from the cricket team, politics will run out",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The President, the Prime Minister and the Members of Parliament of Sri Lanka have lessons to learn from the Sri Lankan cricket team and if the leaders do not learn them, runouts or hits will not be avoided, said MP Dullas Alahapperuma.",
        "He said that no leader or party, including the President, the Prime Minister and the Leader of the Opposition, could save the people from the crisis in the country alone.",
        "Mr. Dullas Alahapperuma said this addressing a meeting with the representatives of the Matara District Local Government Institutions held at the Nupe Head Office recently. He also said,",
        "\"People in our country today have a serious distrust of political parties and leaders. A big, reasonable doubt about honesty has arisen about all politicians. That applies to me too. Family-centric politics has been completely rejected. The only way to overcome the crisis in the long run is to build an advanced, responsible and truly honest political movement that does not lie to the people, does not exploit the country's property, respects public property and recognizes the needs of the 21st century.",
        "Changing the cabinet once a month or changing the prime minister like a pillow for a headache cannot solve this crisis. In the two-and-a-half years since December 2019, he is currently the fifth cabinet and the second prime minister. No leader or party including the President, the Prime Minister, the Leader of the Opposition alone can save the people from this crisis. Therefore, the only thing left for these leaders to do for Sri Lankans is to unite all parties with a short-term, definite economic program for a year. Then the people can be left to decide their own destiny.",
        "The hope of the new generation is to put an end to the culture of \"pickpocketing\" public opinion by mixing sex colors in attractive language. Never let thieves steal votes in any election again. It is the responsibility of the media to expose to the country the education, energy, transport, environmental and agricultural policies of political leaders and parties. Therefore, the statements that we will resolve to vote for us should be discarded as \"rhetorical statements\". If \"a new thief is wanted\" we should go to a theater and not to a polling station."
      ],
